@stoiveyp Turns out that I was doing something  wrong! I thought I had updated, but my code was stuck running version 1.5.5 of the library instead of the latest version where this is no longer an issue. 

Old version (1.5.5 with the issue):

```
public static bool RequestTimestampWithinTolerance(DateTime timestamp)
{
        return Math.Abs(DateTime.Now.Subtract(timestamp).TotalSeconds) <= 150.0;
}
```

New version (1.6.3):

```
public static bool RequestTimestampWithinTolerance(DateTime timestamp)
{
        return Math.Abs(DateTimeOffset.Now.Subtract(timestamp).TotalSeconds) <= AllowedTimestampToleranceInSeconds;
}
```

