For body and list templates you use the new DisplayRenderTemplateDirective class, add your template to that, and attach that to your response before returning a value from your skill. Something like the following

```csharp
            var template = new BodyTemplate1
            {
                Title = "Test Title",
                Token = "BodyTemplate",
                Content = new TemplateContent
                {
                    Primary = new TemplateText {Text = "This is primary text"},
                    Secondary = new TemplateText {Text = "This is secondary text"}
                }
            };

            var response = ResponseBuilder.Tell("This is the speech Alexa will use");
            response.Response.Directives.Add(new DisplayRenderTemplateDirective{Template=template});
```

