@U292124 I have good news, I just implemented the feature in the dev branch by adding property GroupMembershipAttributes to let you specify what LDAP attributes should be used.
It can be configured in PowerShell:
```powershell
Add-Type -AssemblyName "ldapcp, Version=1.0.0.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=80be731bc1a1a740"
$config = [ldapcp.LDAPCPConfig]::GetConfiguration("LDAPCPConfig")
foreach ($ldapServer in $config.LDAPConnectionsProp) {
    $ldapServer.GroupMembershipAttributes = @("member", "equivalentToMe")
}
$config.Update()
```

